#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
#
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# matplotlib
from matplotlib import rc
rc('font', family='AppleGothic')
# Excel
df = pd.read_excel('/Users/shc/Desktop/ / _ _20210226235348.xlsx',
header=0)
# (NaN) ( )
df = df.fillna(method='ffill')
#
mask = (df[''] == ' ') & (df[''] != '')
df_industry = df[mask]
df_industry = df_industry.drop([''], axis=1)
df_industry.rename({'':''}, axis=1, inplace=True)
df_industry.set_index('', inplace=True)
# '29 ','30~39', '40~49', '50~59', '60 '
col_years = list(map(str, range(2018,2019)))
df_5 = df_industry.loc[['29 ','30~39', '40~49', '50~59', '60 '], col_years]
# 2018-2019
df_5[''] = df_5.sum(axis=1)
#
df_total = df_5[['']].sort_values(by='', ascending=True)
#
plt.style.use('ggplot')
#
df_total.plot(kind='barh', color='cornflowerblue', width=0.5, figsize=(10, 5))
plt.title(' (2018~2019)')
plt.ylabel('')
plt.xlabel('')
plt.show() #
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
#
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# matplotlib
from matplotlib import rc
rc('font', family='AppleGothic')
# Excel
df = pd.read_excel('/Users/shc/Desktop/ / _ _20210226235348.xlsx',
header=0)
# (NaN) ( )
df = df.fillna(method='ffill')
#
mask = (df[''] == ' ') & (df[''] != '')
df_industry = df[mask]
df_industry = df_industry.drop([''], axis=1)
df_industry.rename({'':''}, axis=1, inplace=True)
df_industry.set_index('', inplace=True)
# 29
sr_one = df_industry.loc['29 ']
#
plt.style.use('ggplot')
#
plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
# x, y plot
plt.plot(sr_one.index, sr_one.values, marker='o', markersize=10)
#
plt.title(' 29 ', size=24)
#
plt.xlabel('', size=14)
plt.ylabel('', size=14)
plt.legend(labels=['29 '], loc='best', fontsize=10)
plt.show() #
